Middle East]]\n\n{{improve categories|date=December 2018}}\n", "name_user": "Sinaloa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omani_Empire"}
{"title_page": "Joe Wicks (coach)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| Born                = 21 September 1986 (age 33 years)\n| nationality         = British\n| children            = 2\n| education           = [[St Mary's University, Twickenham]]\n| profession          = [[Coach (sport)|Coach]]\n| website             = https://www.thebodycoach.com/\n| residence           = [[Richmond, London|Richmond, South-West London]]\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| spouse              = Rosie Jones\n}}\n\n'''Joe Wicks''' (born 21 September 1986), otherwise known as \"The Body Coach\", is a British [[fitness coach]], TV presenter and author.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/tv/B-g1WNugXrm/|title=World Economic Forum on Instagram: \u201cHave you attended one of Joe's lessons? Learn more by tapping the link in our bio. #coronavirus #covid19 #health #exercise #lockdown\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> His fitness method uses short intense High Intensity Interval Training (HIIT or, colloquially, 'HIT') workouts. Starting off by posting 15-second recipe videos on social media, Wicks grew his brand to become one of the most followed fitness accounts on Instagram and Youtube. His first published cookbook ''Lean in 15: 15-minute meals'' was a best-seller in 2015, having sold over 900,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/active/i-want-to-be-the-voice-that-gets-the-nation-healthy-joe-wicks-on|title='I want to be the voice that gets the nation healthy': Joe Wicks on being the next Jamie Oliver|work=[[Daily Telegraph]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jun/19/lean-in-15-the-shape-plan-by-joe-wicks-digested-read|title='Lean in 15: The Shape Plan by Joe Wicks \u2013 digested read|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref> He has created a \"90 Day Plan\" with workouts and meals with tailored portions to the individual. During the UK [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] lockdown in the United Kingdom he began \"P.E With Joe\" on YouTube to try to help children stay active; this livestream had a wide impact and was viewed by over a million users worldwide.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Bakare|first=Lanre|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/23/a-million-people-livestream-joe-wicks-online-pe-lesson|title=A million people livestream Joe Wicks online 'PE lesson'|date=2020-03-23|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-27|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He is a [[Channel 4]] television presenter with his own show ''The Body Coach''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/joe-wicks-the-body-coach|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nWicks was awarded a [[Guinness World Records|Guiness World Record]] for 'most viewers for a fitness workout live stream on Youtube', after achieving almost a million viewers on 24th March 2020 for his live stream.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/joe-wicks-guinness-world-record-youtube-workouts-102650049.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly9kdWNrZHVja2dvLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAKOCNJHfRAtZZrCV09YxoYKg22bZCb41rIdAHt9wKrBxAM_04dn_a4iXg1Ibab_YgqsCwTGvNe0JiPRyudEYhgRk5aBIY-scO6Nx5NoqJelprvMoy08TR3cD6nzSetWJhroZ1_S6A1IHRC_uO9cLv_KoUpfsGioHwj-4-sSgeD5_|title=Joe Wicks lands Guiness World Record with Youtube workout.|last=|first=|date=|website=Yahoo|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The award was presented to him virtually due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|2020 Coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Early life ==\n\nWicks was born in [[Epsom]], [[Surrey]] to Raquela Mosquera, a social worker, and Gary Wicks, a roofer. His mother is of Italian descent. He grew up on a council estate with his parents and two brothers, Nikki and George<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>.  Wicks' father struggled with drug addiction from a young age and was in and out of rehab causing him to not always be present when Wicks and his brothers were growing up. His father is now sober from drug use after undertaking the 12-step programme.\n\n==== Education ====\nWicks attended [[Blenheim High Scool]] in Epsom, Surrey<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.getsurrey.co.uk/whats-on/whats-on-news/body-coach-joe-wicks-returns-12360218|title=Kids get good food and exercise tips from The Body Coach|last=Nightingale|first=Laura|date=2016-12-23|website=getsurrey|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> and [[NESCOT]] technology college in [[Epsom]].{{cn|date=November 2018}} He went on to study [[sports science]] at [[St Mary's University, Twickenham|St Mary's University]] in [[Twickenham]].\n\n== Personal life ==\nWicks married model Rosie Jones in June of 2019. Together they have 2 children, a daughter, Indie, and a son, Marley.\nHis maternal grandparents were from the [[Isle of Man]].\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/joe-wicks-who-workout-net-worth-wife-rosie-body-coach-youtube-watch-a9429456.html|title=Who is Joe Wicks? The fitness guru is currently leading PE lessons for British kids in lockdown|date=2020-03-27|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nWicks worked as a teaching assistant after completing his [[Sports science]] degree<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> After realising it was not his ideal job, he became a personal trainer for the next five years<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> \n\nJoe received a major boost at the beginning of his business as he received almost \u00a395k from his generous uncle Eddie, which reportedly he paid back within 3 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2016-08-29/joe-wicks-the-body-coach-on-his-rise-to-fame-his-realist-approach-and-his-new-channel-4-show|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach on his rise to fame, his realist approach and his new Channel 4 show|work=[[Radio Times]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nWicks has been a guest on several UK daytime talk shows, including [[Good Morning Britain (2014 TV programme)|Good Morning Britain]] ,[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]],[[Loose Women]] and [[Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pbBeQlkeeA|title=The Body Coach On How To Eat More And Lose Weight {{!}} Good Morning Britain|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ua9JBWsBWc4|title=Joe Wicks' Meat Free Bolognese {{!}} Lorraine|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K1KFFzOlBks|title=Joe Wicks' OMG French Toast {{!}} This Morning|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EUDaXWwWydA|title=Joe Wicks Questioned About His Romantic Life By Katie Price {{!}} Loose Women|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nA segment on [[Channel 4]] named \"Joe Wicks: The Body Coach\" aired in 2016 with Wicks as the presenter. As of 2020 there have been 3 episodes.  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channel4.com/programmes/joe-wicks-the-body-coach|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach: Joe Wicks: The Body Coach|website=Channel 4|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nWicks launched a range of kitchenware in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.meyergroup.co.uk/our-brands/joe-wicks/|title=Joe Wicks|date=2018-08-13|website=Meyer Group Ltd.|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> \n\n==== Online presence ====\nWicks began to gain traction for his fitness and nutrition related content on social media. In 2014 he began posting videos to [[Instagram]] relating to workouts and nutrition advice. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/joe-wicks-journey-skint-pt-fitness-mogul-12461716/|title=Joe Wicks' amazing journey from skint PT to fitness mogul with a \u00a314m empire|date=2020-03-26|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> He has amassed over 3 million followers on his Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/thebodycoach/|title=Joe Wicks (@thebodycoach) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nHe launched a website called The Body Coach where he sells his kitchenware and a range of fitness/nutrition plans. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebodycoach.com/90dayplan/|title=90 Day Plan / The Body Coach|website=www.thebodycoach.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebodycoach.com/|title=Welcome / The Body Coach|website=www.thebodycoach.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> \n\nWicks has been recognised by several major publications, such as [[Harper's Bazaar]], [[Elle (magazine)|Elle UK]] and [[Forbes]] for his online fitness efforts. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/top-influencers/fitness/|title=Top Influencers of 2017: Fitness|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/joe-wicks/|title=Joe Wicks|last=Barton|first=ByMerrilee|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/beauty/fitness-wellbeing/10-of-the-best-instagram-accounts-for-fitness-inspiration|title=10 Instagram accounts to follow for fitness Inspiration|date=2017-01-02|website=Harper's BAZAAR|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elleuk.com/beauty/health-fitness/healthy-breakfast-recipes-lean-in-15-joe-wicks|title=Think outside the cereal box|last=Lawrenson|first=Amy|date=2014-10-03|website=ELLE|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==== Youtube ====\nHe began posting fitness content to his [[Youtube]] channel, named 'The Body Coach TV', in 2014. His first video garnered over 6 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q20pLhdoEoY&t=149s|title=HIIT Home Workout for beginners|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The channel has amassed over 2.2 million subscribers and more than 128 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAxW1XT0iEJo0TYlRfn6rYQ|title=The Body Coach TV|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March 2020 Wicks uploaded a video announcing that he would begin to produce \"P.E with Joe\" videos on his channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K6r99N3kXME|title=Announcing \"P.E with Joe\" {{!}} Daily LIVE workouts for kids {{!}} The Body Coach|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> These videos were exercise videos aimed at children to keep fit during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] as schools were closed. Wicks announced on his Instagram that he will donate profits from these videos to the [[National Health Service|NHS]]. <ref>{{Cite news|last=Association|first=Press|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/mar/28/joe-wicks-body-coach-tv-pe-youtube-nhs-covid-19-lockdown|title=Joe Wicks to donate profits from YouTube PE sessions to NHS|date=2020-03-28|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-P8CO8Dcp7/|title=Joe Wicks on Instagram: \u201cWords can't express how happy and proud I have felt every day this week as the nation\u2019s P.E. teacher. I\u2019ve been overwhelmed with the\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==== Books ====\nIn 2015, Wicks published a cookbook named \"Lean in 15: The Shift Plan\" which sold 77,000 copies in its opening week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/joe-wicks-journey-skint-pt-fitness-mogul-12461716/|title=Joe Wicks' amazing journey from skint PT to fitness mogul with a \u00a314m empire|date=2020-03-26|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> He released a further two books in the \"Lean in 15\" series, including \"Lean in 15: The Shape Plan\", released 2016 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/work/best_book/48727628-lean-in-15---the-shape-plan-15-minute-meals-with-workouts-to-build-a-st|title=Lean in 15 - The Shape Plan|website=www.goodreads.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>  and \"Lean in 15: The Sustain Plan\", also in 2016. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.panmacmillan.com/%20/authors/joe-wicks/lean-in-15-the-sustain-plan/9781509820221|title=Lean in 15 - The Sustain Plan by Joe Wicks|website=Pan Macmillan|language=English|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nSince the success of the \"Lean in 15\" series, Wicks has published several more cookbooks. His upcoming cookbook, \"Wean in 15\" is set to be released in May,2020 and will focus on 'weaning babies onto solid food and recipes for time-pressed parents'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/healthandbeauty/mother-and-baby/2019052273364/joe-wicks-the-body-coach-shares-parenting-tips-weaning/|title=The Body Coach and new dad, Joe Wicks, reveals his family plans and weaning tips|date=2019-05-22|website=HELLO!|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/news/wicks-wean-15-872051|title=Wicks to Wean in 15 {{!}} The Bookseller|website=www.thebookseller.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Title\n!Publisher\n!ISBN\n|-\n|2015\n|Lean in 15 - The Shift Plan: 15 Minute Meals and Workouts to Keep You Lean and Healthy\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509800667|}} \n(Paperback, 224 pages)\n|-\n|2016\n|Lean in 15 - The Shape Plan: 15 Minute Meals With Workouts to Build a Strong, Lean Body\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509800698|}}\n\n(Paperback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2016\n|Lean in 15 - The Sustain Plan: 15 Minute Meals and Workouts to Get You Lean for Life\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509820221|}}\n(Paperback, 240 pages)\n|-\n|2017\n|The Fat Loss Plan:100 Quick and Easy Recipes With Workouts\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509836079|}}\n(Paperback, 240 pages)\n|-\n|2017\n|Cooking for Family and Friends: 100 Lean Recipes to Enjoy Together\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509820252|}}\n(Hardback,240 pages) \n|-\n|2018\n|Joe's 30 Minute Meals: 100 Quick and Healthy Recipes\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781785175121|}}\n(Hardback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2018\n|Veggie Lean in 15: 15-minute Veggie Meals with Workouts\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509856152|}}\n(Paperback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2019\n|Veggie BBQ: 10 Brand-new Lean in 15 Recipes\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509856176|}}\n(E-book, 32 pages)\n|-\n|2020\n(TBR)\n|Wean In 15\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781529016338|}} \n(Hardback, 240 pages)\n|}\n\n\n\n<br />\n\n= References =\n{{reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.thebodycoach.co.uk/}}\n*{{official website|https://befitnesshub.com/workouts-for-weight-loss-beginners/}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wicks, Joe}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Channel 4 people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Diet food advocates]]\n[[Category:English food writers]]\n[[Category:English television chefs]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:Alumni of St Mary's University, Twickenham]]\n[[Category:English people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Manx descent]]\n\n{{England-tv-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| Born                = 21 September 1986 (age 33 years)\n| nationality         = British\n| children            = 2\n| education           = [[St Mary's University, Twickenham]]\n| profession          = [[Coach (sport)|Coach]]\n| website             = https://www.thebodycoach.com/\n| residence           = [[Richmond, London|Richmond, South-West London]]\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| spouse              = Rosie Jones\n}}\n\n'''Joe Wicks''' (born 21 September 1986), otherwise known as \"The Body Coach\", is a British [[fitness coach]], TV presenter and author.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/tv/B-g1WNugXrm/|title=World Economic Forum on Instagram: \u201cHave you attended one of Joe's lessons? Learn more by tapping the link in our bio. #coronavirus #covid19 #health #exercise #lockdown\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> His fitness method uses short intense High Intensity Interval Training (HIIT or, colloquially, 'HIT') workouts. Starting off by posting 15-second recipe videos on social media, Wicks grew his brand to become one of the most followed fitness accounts on Instagram and Youtube. His first published cookbook ''Lean in 15: 15-minute meals'' was a best-seller in 2015, having sold over 900,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/active/i-want-to-be-the-voice-that-gets-the-nation-healthy-joe-wicks-on|title='I want to be the voice that gets the nation healthy': Joe Wicks on being the next Jamie Oliver|work=[[Daily Telegraph]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jun/19/lean-in-15-the-shape-plan-by-joe-wicks-digested-read|title='Lean in 15: The Shape Plan by Joe Wicks \u2013 digested read|publisher=[[The Guardian]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref> He has created a \"90 Day Plan\" with workouts and meals with tailored portions to the individual. During the UK [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] lockdown in the United Kingdom he began \"P.E With Joe\" on YouTube to try to help children stay active; this livestream had a wide impact and was viewed by over a million users worldwide.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Bakare|first=Lanre|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/23/a-million-people-livestream-joe-wicks-online-pe-lesson|title=A million people livestream Joe Wicks online 'PE lesson'|date=2020-03-23|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-27|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He is a [[Channel 4]] television presenter with his own show ''The Body Coach''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/joe-wicks-the-body-coach|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nWicks was awarded a [[Guinness World Records|Guiness World Record]] for 'most viewers for a fitness workout live stream on Youtube', after achieving almost a million viewers on 24th March 2020 for his live stream.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/joe-wicks-guinness-world-record-youtube-workouts-102650049.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly9kdWNrZHVja2dvLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAKOCNJHfRAtZZrCV09YxoYKg22bZCb41rIdAHt9wKrBxAM_04dn_a4iXg1Ibab_YgqsCwTGvNe0JiPRyudEYhgRk5aBIY-scO6Nx5NoqJelprvMoy08TR3cD6nzSetWJhroZ1_S6A1IHRC_uO9cLv_KoUpfsGioHwj-4-sSgeD5_|title=Joe Wicks lands Guiness World Record with Youtube workout.|last=|first=|date=|website=Yahoo|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The award was presented to him virtually due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|2020 Coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Early life ==\n\nWicks was born in [[Epsom]], [[Surrey]] to Raquela Mosquera, a social worker, and Gary Wicks, a roofer. His mother is of Italian descent. He grew up on a council estate with his parents and two brothers, Nikki and George<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>.  Wicks' father struggled with drug addiction from a young age and was in and out of rehab causing him to not always be present when Wicks and his brothers were growing up. His father is now sober from drug use after undertaking the 12-step programme.\n\n==== Education ====\nWicks attended [[Blenheim High School]] in Epsom, Surrey<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.getsurrey.co.uk/whats-on/whats-on-news/body-coach-joe-wicks-returns-12360218|title=Kids get good food and exercise tips from The Body Coach|last=Nightingale|first=Laura|date=2016-12-23|website=getsurrey|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> and [[NESCOT]] technology college in [[Epsom]].{{cn|date=November 2018}} He went on to study [[sports science]] at [[St Mary's University, Twickenham|St Mary's University]] in [[Twickenham]].\n\n== Personal life ==\nWicks married model Rosie Jones in June of 2019. Together they have 2 children, a daughter, Indie, and a son, Marley.\nHis maternal grandparents were from the [[Isle of Man]].\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/joe-wicks-who-workout-net-worth-wife-rosie-body-coach-youtube-watch-a9429456.html|title=Who is Joe Wicks? The fitness guru is currently leading PE lessons for British kids in lockdown|date=2020-03-27|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nWicks worked as a teaching assistant after completing his [[Sports science]] degree<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> After realising it was not his ideal job, he became a personal trainer for the next five years<ref>{{Cite news|last=Heritage|first=Stuart|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2016/jun/18/joe-wicks-meet-body-coach-million-dollar-muscles|title=Meet the Body Coach, the man with the million-dollar muscles|date=2016-06-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> \n\nJoe received a major boost at the beginning of his business as he received almost \u00a395k from his generous uncle Eddie, which reportedly he paid back within 3 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2016-08-29/joe-wicks-the-body-coach-on-his-rise-to-fame-his-realist-approach-and-his-new-channel-4-show|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach on his rise to fame, his realist approach and his new Channel 4 show|work=[[Radio Times]]|access-date=29 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nWicks has been a guest on several UK daytime talk shows, including [[Good Morning Britain (2014 TV programme)|Good Morning Britain]] ,[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]],[[Loose Women]] and [[Lorraine (TV programme)|Lorraine]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pbBeQlkeeA|title=The Body Coach On How To Eat More And Lose Weight {{!}} Good Morning Britain|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ua9JBWsBWc4|title=Joe Wicks' Meat Free Bolognese {{!}} Lorraine|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K1KFFzOlBks|title=Joe Wicks' OMG French Toast {{!}} This Morning|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EUDaXWwWydA|title=Joe Wicks Questioned About His Romantic Life By Katie Price {{!}} Loose Women|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nA segment on [[Channel 4]] named \"Joe Wicks: The Body Coach\" aired in 2016 with Wicks as the presenter. As of 2020 there have been 3 episodes.  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channel4.com/programmes/joe-wicks-the-body-coach|title=Joe Wicks: The Body Coach: Joe Wicks: The Body Coach|website=Channel 4|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nWicks launched a range of kitchenware in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.meyergroup.co.uk/our-brands/joe-wicks/|title=Joe Wicks|date=2018-08-13|website=Meyer Group Ltd.|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> \n\n==== Online presence ====\nWicks began to gain traction for his fitness and nutrition related content on social media. In 2014 he began posting videos to [[Instagram]] relating to workouts and nutrition advice. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/joe-wicks-journey-skint-pt-fitness-mogul-12461716/|title=Joe Wicks' amazing journey from skint PT to fitness mogul with a \u00a314m empire|date=2020-03-26|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> He has amassed over 3 million followers on his Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/thebodycoach/|title=Joe Wicks (@thebodycoach) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nHe launched a website called The Body Coach where he sells his kitchenware and a range of fitness/nutrition plans. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebodycoach.com/90dayplan/|title=90 Day Plan / The Body Coach|website=www.thebodycoach.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebodycoach.com/|title=Welcome / The Body Coach|website=www.thebodycoach.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> \n\nWicks has been recognised by several major publications, such as [[Harper's Bazaar]], [[Elle (magazine)|Elle UK]] and [[Forbes]] for his online fitness efforts. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/top-influencers/fitness/|title=Top Influencers of 2017: Fitness|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/joe-wicks/|title=Joe Wicks|last=Barton|first=ByMerrilee|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.co.uk/beauty/fitness-wellbeing/10-of-the-best-instagram-accounts-for-fitness-inspiration|title=10 Instagram accounts to follow for fitness Inspiration|date=2017-01-02|website=Harper's BAZAAR|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elleuk.com/beauty/health-fitness/healthy-breakfast-recipes-lean-in-15-joe-wicks|title=Think outside the cereal box|last=Lawrenson|first=Amy|date=2014-10-03|website=ELLE|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==== Youtube ====\nHe began posting fitness content to his [[Youtube]] channel, named 'The Body Coach TV', in 2014. His first video garnered over 6 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q20pLhdoEoY&t=149s|title=HIIT Home Workout for beginners|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The channel has amassed over 2.2 million subscribers and more than 128 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCAxW1XT0iEJo0TYlRfn6rYQ|title=The Body Coach TV|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March 2020 Wicks uploaded a video announcing that he would begin to produce \"P.E with Joe\" videos on his channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K6r99N3kXME|title=Announcing \"P.E with Joe\" {{!}} Daily LIVE workouts for kids {{!}} The Body Coach|last=|first=|date=|website=Youtube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> These videos were exercise videos aimed at children to keep fit during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] as schools were closed. Wicks announced on his Instagram that he will donate profits from these videos to the [[National Health Service|NHS]]. <ref>{{Cite news|last=Association|first=Press|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/mar/28/joe-wicks-body-coach-tv-pe-youtube-nhs-covid-19-lockdown|title=Joe Wicks to donate profits from YouTube PE sessions to NHS|date=2020-03-28|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-P8CO8Dcp7/|title=Joe Wicks on Instagram: \u201cWords can't express how happy and proud I have felt every day this week as the nation\u2019s P.E. teacher. I\u2019ve been overwhelmed with the\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==== Books ====\nIn 2015, Wicks published a cookbook named \"Lean in 15: The Shift Plan\" which sold 77,000 copies in its opening week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/joe-wicks-journey-skint-pt-fitness-mogul-12461716/|title=Joe Wicks' amazing journey from skint PT to fitness mogul with a \u00a314m empire|date=2020-03-26|website=Metro|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> He released a further two books in the \"Lean in 15\" series, including \"Lean in 15: The Shape Plan\", released 2016 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodreads.com/work/best_book/48727628-lean-in-15---the-shape-plan-15-minute-meals-with-workouts-to-build-a-st|title=Lean in 15 - The Shape Plan|website=www.goodreads.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>  and \"Lean in 15: The Sustain Plan\", also in 2016. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.panmacmillan.com/%20/authors/joe-wicks/lean-in-15-the-sustain-plan/9781509820221|title=Lean in 15 - The Sustain Plan by Joe Wicks|website=Pan Macmillan|language=English|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nSince the success of the \"Lean in 15\" series, Wicks has published several more cookbooks. His upcoming cookbook, \"Wean in 15\" is set to be released in May,2020 and will focus on 'weaning babies onto solid food and recipes for time-pressed parents'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/healthandbeauty/mother-and-baby/2019052273364/joe-wicks-the-body-coach-shares-parenting-tips-weaning/|title=The Body Coach and new dad, Joe Wicks, reveals his family plans and weaning tips|date=2019-05-22|website=HELLO!|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebookseller.com/news/wicks-wean-15-872051|title=Wicks to Wean in 15 {{!}} The Bookseller|website=www.thebookseller.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Title\n!Publisher\n!ISBN\n|-\n|2015\n|Lean in 15 - The Shift Plan: 15 Minute Meals and Workouts to Keep You Lean and Healthy\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509800667|}} \n(Paperback, 224 pages)\n|-\n|2016\n|Lean in 15 - The Shape Plan: 15 Minute Meals With Workouts to Build a Strong, Lean Body\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509800698|}}\n\n(Paperback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2016\n|Lean in 15 - The Sustain Plan: 15 Minute Meals and Workouts to Get You Lean for Life\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509820221|}}\n(Paperback, 240 pages)\n|-\n|2017\n|The Fat Loss Plan:100 Quick and Easy Recipes With Workouts\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509836079|}}\n(Paperback, 240 pages)\n|-\n|2017\n|Cooking for Family and Friends: 100 Lean Recipes to Enjoy Together\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509820252|}}\n(Hardback,240 pages) \n|-\n|2018\n|Joe's 30 Minute Meals: 100 Quick and Healthy Recipes\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781785175121|}}\n(Hardback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2018\n|Veggie Lean in 15: 15-minute Veggie Meals with Workouts\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509856152|}}\n(Paperback,240 pages)\n|-\n|2019\n|Veggie BBQ: 10 Brand-new Lean in 15 Recipes\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781509856176|}}\n(E-book, 32 pages)\n|-\n|2020\n(TBR)\n|Wean In 15\n|Pan Macmillan\n|{{ISBN|9781529016338|}} \n(Hardback, 240 pages)\n|}\n\n\n\n<br />\n\n= References =\n{{reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n==External links==\n*{{official website|http://www.thebodycoach.co.uk/}}\n*{{official website|https://befitnesshub.com/workouts-for-weight-loss-beginners/}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wicks, Joe}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Channel 4 people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Diet food advocates]]\n[[Category:English food writers]]\n[[Category:English television chefs]]\n[[Category:English television presenters]]\n[[Category:Alumni of St Mary's University, Twickenham]]\n[[Category:English people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Manx descent]]\n\n{{England-tv-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c4:170b:5300:7d85:2015:68a9:b45d", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEducation)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Wicks_(coach)"}
{"title_page": "Parombo", "text_new": "{{short description|Town in Uganda}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          = Parombo\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = <!--For Town or Village (Leave blank for the default City)-->\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = \n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|image_map1             = \n|mapsize1               = \n|map_caption1           = \n|image_dot_map          =\n|dot_mapsize            =\n|dot_map_caption        =\n|dot_x =  |dot_y =\n|pushpin_map            = Uganda<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in Uganda<br/>'''Placement on map is approximate'''\n<!-- Location ------------------>\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Image:Flag of Uganda.svg|25px]] [[Uganda]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Regions of Uganda|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1 \u00a0 \u00a0  = [[Northern Region, Uganda|Northern Uganda]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Districts of Uganda|District]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Nebbi District]]\n|subdivision_type3      = [[Towns in Uganda|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name3      = Parombo\n|subdivision_type4      = [[County]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|subdivision_type5      = [[Parliament of Uganda|Constituency]]\n|subdivision_name5      = \n|subdivision_type6      = \n|subdivision_name6      =\n<!-- Politics ----------------->\n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name            = \n|leader_title1          = [[Parliament of Uganda|MP]]\n|leader_name1           = \n|leader_title2          =\n|leader_name2           =\n|leader_title3          =\n|leader_name3           =\n|leader_title4          =\n|leader_name4           =\n|established_title      =  <!-- Settled -->\n|established_date       = \n|established_title2     =  <!-- Incorporated (town) -->\n|established_date2      = \n|established_title3     =  <!-- Incorporated (city) -->\n|established_date3      =\n<!-- Area    --------------------->\n|area_magnitude         = \n|unit_pref                =Imperial <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = <!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion-->\n|area_land_km2            = <!--See table @ Template:Infobox Settlement for details on automatic unit conversion-->\n|area_water_km2           =\n|area_total_sq_mi         =\n|area_land_sq_mi          =\n|area_water_sq_mi         =\n|area_water_percent       =\n|area_urban_km2           =\n|area_urban_sq_mi         =\n|area_metro_km2           =\n|area_metro_sq_mi         =\n|area_blank1_title        =\n|area_blank1_km2          =\n|area_blank1_sq_mi        =\n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n|population_as_of               = 2014 (Census)\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               =\n|population_density_km2         =\n|population_density_sq_mi       =\n|population_metro               =\n|population_density_metro_km2   =\n|population_density_metro_sq_mi =\n|population_urban               = \n|population_density_urban_km2   =\n|population_density_urban_sq_mi =\n|population_blank1_title        =Ethnicities\n|population_blank1              =\n|population_blank2_title        =Religions\n|population_blank2              =\n|population_density_blank1_km2 =   \n|population_density_blank1_sq_mi =\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = \n|utc_offset             = \n|timezone_DST           = \n|utc_offset_DST         =\n|coordinates            = {{coord|02|18|13|N|31|12|11|E|region:UG|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            = 969\n|elevation_ft           =\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|blank1_name            =\n|blank1_info            =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}} \n\n'''Parombo''' is a town in the [[West Nile sub-region]] of the [[Northern Region, Uganda|Northern Region]] of [[Uganda]].<ref name=\"1R\">{{cite web|url=http://uganda.places-in-the-world.com/226787-place-Parombo.html |title=Parombo is a place in the Northern Region in Uganda |publisher=Places In The World: Parombo, Uganda |date=20 April 2020 |author=Places In The World | access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nParombo is located in Jonam County, ''Parombo Subcounty'', in [[Nebbi District]], in northwestern Uganda. It is approximately {{convert|12|km|0}}, by road, north of the international border with the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. This location is approximately {{convert|34|km|0}}, by road, southeast of [[Nebbi]], where the district headquarters are located.<ref name=\"2R\">{{google maps|access-date=20 April 2020 | url=https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Nebbi/Parombo/@2.3983304,31.1896196,9.96z/data=!4m14!4m13!1m5!1m1!1s0x176fbad301a3d3fb:0x6636d34b48c389a4!2m2!1d31.0851019!2d2.4778169!1m5!1m1!1s0x176f94733699bda3:0x7ac4c4aac9d314e9!2m2!1d31.2025336!2d2.3021193!3e0 |\ntitle=Driving Distance Between Nebbi And Parombo}}</ref> The geographical coordinates of Parombo are:02\u00b018'13.0\"N, 31\u00b012'11.0\"E (Latitude:2.303611; Longitude:31.203056).<ref name=\"3R\">{{google maps|title=Location of Parombo, Uganda | url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/2%C2%B018'13.0%22N+31%C2%B012'11.0%22E/@2.2787395,31.1912083,13.29z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d2.3036111!4d31.2030556 |access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref> Parombo sits at an average elevation of {{convert|969|m|0}} above sea level.<ref name=\"4R\">{{cite web|title=Elevation of Parombo, Uganda |url=https://www.floodmap.net/Elevation/ElevationMap/?gi=226787 |date=20 April 2020 |access-date=20 April 2020 | publisher=Floodmap.net |author=Floodmap.net}}</ref>\n\n== Overview ==\nParombo is divided into six administrative divisions; namely (a) Parwo (b) Pagwata (c) Ossi (d) Padel (e) Pangarere and (f) Pulum.\nThe growing urban area has a town board.<ref name=\"5R\">{{cite web |url=http://mlhud.go.ug/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/PAROMBO-TOWN-BOARD-PHYSICAL-DEVELOPMENT-PLAN-2012-2022.pdf |title=Parombo Town Board, Physical Development Plan 2012 - 2022 |publisher=[[Ministry of Lands, Housing and Urban Development (Uganda)]] | \nauthor=Uganda Ministry of Lands, Housing and Urban Development | date=2011 |access-date=20 April 2020 |location=Kampala}}</ref>\n\n==Population==\nThe national population census and household survey, carried out on 27 August 2014, enumerated the population of ''Parombo Subcounty'' at 41,286 people. This population is mainly rural and the urban centre is a much smaller fraction of the sub-county.<ref name=\"6R\">{{cite web |title=Uganda Water Supply Atlas: District Report For Nebbi District |date=19 April 2020 | url=http://wsdb.mwe.go.ug/index.php/reports/district/26 | publisher=[[Ministry of Water and Environment (Uganda)]] | author=Uganda Ministry of Water & Environment |access-date=20 April 2020 |place=Kampala}}</ref> The majority of inhabitants of the sub-county and the town are the [[Alur people]].<ref name=\"7R\">{{cite web|title=Zziwa, Byamukama mere pawns in political game |newspaper=[[The Observer (Uganda)]] |\nurl=https://www.observer.ug/component/content/article?id=19532:zziwa-byamukama-mere-pawns-in-political-game |date=28 June 2012 |author=Charles Odongtho |access-date=20 April 2020 | location=Kampala}}</ref>\n\n==Challenges==\nTwo of the most challenging issues for Parombo are water scarcity and poor sanitation. The water crisis in Parombo and surrounding communities dates back for nearly two decades.<ref name=\"8R\">{{cite web |url=https://allafrica.com/stories/200612181585.html | date=19 December 2006 |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |author=Felix Warom Okello |access-date=20 April 2020 |title=Uganda: Nebbi Sends SOS to Govt On Water Crisis |format=via [[AllAfrica.com]]}}</ref><ref name=\"9R\">{{cite web|title=Alwi Corridor\u2019s Water Crisis |newspaper=[[Daily Monitor]] |date=2 May 2011 | url=https://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Entertainment/812796-1154108-11mmb45/index.html |author=Felix Warom Okello |access-date=20 April 2020 |location=Kampala}}</ref><ref name=\"10R\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Uganda Radio Network]] |date=16 March 2012 |url=https://ugandaradionetwork.com/story/residents-block-construction-of-gravity-water-project |title=Residents Block Construction of Gravity Water Project |author=Patrick Okaba |access-date=20 April 2020 |place=Kampala}}</ref> The town and surrounding areas have protected springs, shallow wells and boreholes from which they collect water for animal and human use. But these infrastructure developments do not meet all the area's water needs.<ref name=\"11R\">{{cite web|newspaper=[[New Vision]] | url=https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1060804/nebbi-district-protected-water |title=Nebbi District Gets Protected Water |newspaper=[[New Vision]] |date=19 March 2002 |author=New Vision |access-date=20 April 2020 |location=Kampala}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, [[National Water and Sewerage Corporation]] (NWSC) was tasked to establish a piped water system in Parombo Town Council and in the surrounding communities.<ref name=\"12R\">{{cite web| url=https://www.monitor.co.ug/News/National/NWSC-asked-to-take-over-Alwi-water-project/688334-4861058-yv73pcz/index.html | \ntitle=NWSC Asked To Take Over Alwi Water Project |date=21 November 2018 |author=Patrick Okaba |access-date=20 April 2020 | location=Kampala}}</ref> Work is continuing, although initial attempts to locate a suitable water source have been unsuccessful.<ref name=\"13R\">{{cite web|date=29 July 2019 | url=https://www.westnileweb.com/news-a-analysis/nebbi/parombo-water-project-hits-a-snag |title=Parombo Water Project Hits A Snag |publisher=West Nile Web |access-date=20 April 2020 | author=Prisca Oroma |location=Arua}}</ref>\n\nDue to the absence of a centralized sewerage disposal system, sanitation remains a challenge as sometimes sewage contaminates water sources for human consumption, as happened at Parombo Secondary School in March 2019.<ref name=\"14R\">{{cite web| url=https://ugandaradionetwork.net/story/latrine-crisis-hits-parombo-ss- |title=Latrine Crisis Hits Parombo SS |date=20 March 2019 |publisher=[[Uganda Radio Network]] |access-date=20 April 2020 |author=Ronald Orachwun |place=Kampala}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.newvision.co.ug/new_vision/news/1503276/voting-opposition-waste-museveni Voting opposition is waste of time, says Museveni] As of 10 July 2019. \n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Nebbi District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Uganda]]\n[[Category:West Nile sub-region]]\n[[Category:Nebbi District]]\n[[Category:Northern Region, Uganda]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Town in Uganda}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          = Parombo\n|other_name             =\n|nati